Packing pic 1/3 ? so as always I'm packing last minute haha ? I thought I would show you how/what I pack for a big trip! ?? I'm actually gone for 3 weeks, and am only taking the one suitcase so I try to pack versatile outfits and accessories. Here you can see I just chose silver, so everything matches and I don't have to think about it. I popped a lil color in there with my @danielwellington watches, but other than that it's all quite dainty and simple! ? @theofficialpandora rings, some @whitefoxboutique hoop earrings, another watch which is @katespadeny, @quayaustralia sunnies from wfb, a silver choker from @missguided, a couple of bracelets inc my @tiffanyandco one that was gifted to me by @benefitnz, and a couple other random necklaces in different styles ? since it's mostly dainty it doesn't weigh much either, and I'm transporting it all in this cute @themintrepublic box! ??? #shaaanxo ? #packing #jewelry #danielwellington #pandora #love

???"Lo conoscete questo simbolo?Si chiama Khamsa o più comunemente La Mano di Fatima.
La leggenda narra che una sera Fatima stava preparando la cena, quando il marito rientrò a casa con una concubina.
Per chi non lo sapesse, per la religione islamica l’uomo si può sposare quattro volte.
Fatima, fu così turbata dall' arrivo di questa donna che non si accorse minimamente che il cucchiaio di legno gli era caduto dentro la pentola e che stava mescolando il semolino direttamente con la mano.
Il dolore che provava per amore era talmente grande che non sentiva alcun bruciore.Ed allora ho iniziato a pensare, a quanto siano forti le Donne. Al loro autocontrollo. Alle loro capacità.Forse il cuore delle Donne non è un cuore normale, non ci sono 4 stanze, nessun atrio e nessun ventricolo. Forse è open space… così ci entrano più cose, più persone, più sentimenti. Più dolore.Mi immagino Fatima, con la mano immersa nel semolino ed il cuore nel silenzio.
La grandezza delle Donne, sta nella loro Forza. Le Donne forti le senti appena arrivano: portano con se i propri sogni, le cicatrici, le lacrime, i sorrisi. E quando se ne vanno si percepisce il vuoto.Le Donne sono talmente forti che riescono a trasformare il Niente in Tutto ed ogni notte, alla stessa ora, cominciano a contare le stelle convinte che nulla sia impossibile." #buonaNotte#manodifatima#foramalocchiu#nonegativevibes girlpower#strong#smile#resilienza#instagram#bracelets#pandora#charmpandora#charmspandora#jewels#accessorize#me#girl#tattoo#tattooedgirl

Few days ago, we got an opportunity to visit this beautiful village of Naringgul, South Cianjur regency of West Java. Locals call this place "Village of 1000 Waterfalls". This video quite explains why. And it only captured a glimpse of it. If you want to feel the whole experience, just drive from Bandung City towards Ciwidey, past Kawah Putih and then Rancabali Tea Farm, then a few minutes more..voila! You will arrive at Naringgul Village, Village of 1000 Waterfalls.
You thought landscapes of Planet Pandora in James Cameron's movie Avatar weren't real? Well, they are real here, at Naringgul, West Java, Indonesia.
West Java are waiting for you to explore.. And if you were lucky enough to visit Sukabumi, don't forget to book your rooms at Arondari Hotel. Call us at (+62)266218592 or book us online at Traveloka.com or Agoda.com.

WARNING, this is not a healthy recipe!  That's right, this time of year I use my 80/20 rule with family in town & celebration & love all around????. This rule has become my "bestest" friend in staying on track with my health & fitness.  80% of the day I eat sensibly and make healthy choices, make sure to get my daily dose of dense nutrition with Shakeology and exercise.  The other 20% I enjoy holiday food & drink & I don't feel guilty for it!  Not. One. Bit.  Looking at this journey as a lifestyle vs a diet and being consistent is what I'm all about & how I want to authentically coach others!

SO, what is this amazing recipe, you ask?!?!? OMG-SO good!!! Great for a side dish or appetizer ?? and tag a friend who might enjoy this & encourage them to use the 80/20 rule!

Bacon Crescent wrapped Asparagus
______________________________
-1 package of bacon
-1 bundle of asparagus
-1 roll of crescents - EVOO
-Italian seasoning
-sea salt -Adult beverage (this is for you to drink while you assemble)

1. Blanche asparagus, salt & put aside
2. Cut bacon in half lengthwise 
3. Roll out dough and cut strips (we eyeballed this based on the # of asparagus we had)
4. Get a friend of family member, fix them an adult beverage, find a great station on #pandora & get to wrapping both the bacon & dough!  Think assembly line style
5. Drizzle or spray your EVOO and Italian seasoning
6. Bake at 350 for 20+ mins until golden brown!
7. Enjoy & COME BACK to this post to tell me what you thought!
